    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-17T14:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-17T14:41:00-05:00" n="201"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <head>201. Telegram From <gloss type="from">Operation <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in
                        Florida</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Station</gloss> in [<hi rend="italic"
                        >place not declassified</hi>]<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d201fn1"
                        >Source: Central Intelligence Agency, Job 79–01025A, Box 6, Folder 1.
                        Secret; Immediate; RYBAT; <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1"
                        >PBSUCCESS</gloss>. Repeated to the Director of Central Intelligence, <gloss
                            target="#t_SHERWOOD1">SHERWOOD</gloss>, and to Stations in [<hi
                            rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], Guatemala City, and [<hi
                            rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>].</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-17T19:41:00+00:00">June 17, 1954,
                        1941Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>3966. Command msg for <persName corresp="#p_CIG1">Cadick</persName>: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>You hereby assigned full field command all <gloss target="#t_KUBARK1"
                                >KUBARK</gloss> controlled <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1"
                                >PBSUCCESS</gloss> assets less GUAT Station.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Your mission is to create maximum impact on enemy govt with forces at
                            your disposal. With objective of persuading army to join friendly
                            cause.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>You will be guided by existing directives and/or policies.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>You will be directly responsible to <persName>LINCOLN</persName> for
                            requesting further guidance. <persName>LINCOLN</persName> will provide
                            command directives as required which must be strictly adhered to in
                            every instance.</item>
                        <pb facs="0377" n="347" xml:id="pg_347"/>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>You will hereafter direct all air operational support activities
                            through Somerset less fire. Fighter aircraft will be armed for defense
                            only. Air fire support authority must be obtained from
                                <persName>LINCOLN</persName> regardless of urgency existing.</item>
                        <label>6.</label>
                        <item>You will utilize and employ <gloss target="#t_SHERWOOD1"
                                >Sherwood</gloss> broadcast and <gloss target="#t_KUGOWN1"
                                >KUGOWN</gloss> teams as required.</item>
                        <label>7.</label>
                        <item>You will direct tactical intelligence activities keeping <gloss
                                target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> informed at all times.</item>
                        <label>8.</label>
                        <item>You will submit operational situation report by <gloss
                                target="#t_OPIM1">OPIM</gloss> cable every 12 hours until further
                            notice.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
